# Copy to ".env" or ".env.local" (do not commit secrets). Restart `npm run dev` after changes.



# --- Ollama (local, recommended with Vite proxy — no API key) ---

# 1) Install and start Ollama: https://ollama.com

# 2) Pull a model: ollama pull llama3.2

# 3) Use this base URL during `npm run dev` (see vite.config.ts proxy `/ollama` → port 11434):

VITE_LLM_BASE_URL=/ollama/v1

VITE_LLM_MODEL=llama3.2

# VITE_LLM_API_KEY=



# If your Ollama allows browser CORS, you can call it directly instead of the proxy:

# VITE_LLM_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1

# VITE_LLM_MODEL=llama3.2



# --- Hosted OpenAI-compatible APIs (example: Groq) ---

# VITE_LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1

# VITE_LLM_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# VITE_LLM_API_KEY=your_groq_key



# Optional tuning

# VITE_LLM_MAX_TOKENS=6144  (default 6144 if unset for longer doc-grounded answers; lower on cheap APIs)

# VITE_LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.2



# Production: `VITE_*` is bundled into the client. Prefer a backend proxy for API keys.

# A relative `/ollama/v1` URL only works if your production server forwards `/ollama` to Ollama.

# --- LangChain + Chroma RAG (recommended for “plain RAG” over uploads) ---
# During `npm run dev`, if you omit this variable, the app defaults to `/api/rag` (Vite → port 8000).
# For production builds, set an explicit URL (or leave unset to disable RAG client-side).
# VITE_RAG_API_URL=/api/rag
# Run: `npm run rag:dev`  |  Copy `server/.env.example` → `server/.env` (Ollama embeddings, CHROMA_PATH). Never put secrets in VITE_*.

# --- eFront learning host (optional; in-chat “Open learning environment login” button) ---
# VITE_EFRONT_LEARNING_LOGIN_URL=http://your-host:8081/Login.aspx
# During `npm run dev` only, that button also POSTs to /__kb/run-efront-e2e to spawn Playwright locally (no env flag required).

